E2E Live Supabase Run — 2026-05-15

## Run result

Test: finance-governance-live-supabase.spec.ts
Status: FAIL — design gap identified

Error: element(s) not found
  > await expect(page.locator('tr', { hasText: 'APR-1001' })).toBeVisible()

## Root cause

The test sets `window.localStorage.setItem('finance-governance-demo-org-id', ...)` expecting
the workflow page to use it for API requests. But the current implementation:

- `/finance-governance/live/workflow` uses plain `fetch` with no localStorage injection
- `/api/finance-governance/approvals` calls `getOrg()` which requires a real Supabase auth session
- With no session, the API returns 401 → the page shows an error → `APR-1001` row never appears

This is a test design gap vs. production code drift, not a production defect.

